Module com.example

Class Settings

java.lang.Object
com.example.data.Settings
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Settings extends Object implements Serializable
The Settings class represents the configuration settings for an employee's wages and bonuses. These settings include the hourly wage, extra amount, evening and night bonuses, and tax percentage. This class is serializable, meaning it can be converted into a stream of bytes for storage or transmission.
Author:
Matti Voutilainen
